dcterms:description: The DAIC-WoZ database is a collection of audio-visual interviews in English featuring 189 participants, both male and female, who underwent psychological distress evaluations. The dataset contains 107 speakers used for training and 35 speakers used for evaluation, with audio data extracted from only the patients using provided time labels.
dcterms:title: DAIC-WoZ
